			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the difference between chin implants and genioplasty?</h3>
					<p>Chin implants involve placing a biocompatible material over the chin bone to enhance its shape, while genioplasty repositions the chin bone itself. Implants are simpler and reversible, while genioplasty provides permanent results using your own bone. Dr. Johar will recommend the best option based on your anatomy and goals.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long does chin augmentation surgery take?</h3>
					<p>The procedure typically takes one to two hours, depending on whether implants or genioplasty is used. It is performed on an outpatient basis, allowing you to go home the same day.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long is the recovery after chin augmentation?</h3>
					<p>Most patients can return to work and normal activities within one to two weeks. Full recovery takes one to three months, during which any residual swelling subsides and the final results become apparent.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are chin augmentation results permanent?</h3>
					<p>Chin implants provide long-lasting results, though they can be removed or replaced if desired. Genioplasty results are permanent since they involve repositioning your own bone. Both techniques offer durable outcomes that enhance facial harmony for years.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will chin augmentation make my face look unnatural?</h3>
					<p>When performed by an experienced surgeon like Dr. Johar, chin augmentation produces natural-looking results that complement your existing facial features. The goal is to enhance balance and proportion, not to create an artificial appearance.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can chin augmentation be combined with other procedures?</h3>
					<p>Yes, chin augmentation is often combined with rhinoplasty, facelifts, or neck liposuction for comprehensive facial rejuvenation. Combining procedures can enhance overall results and reduce total recovery time.</p>
